# Session Transcript Extraction Rules

These transcripts are voice-to-text captures of a Spanish-language D&D campaign ("Frozen Sick"). Names are frequently garbled. Apply these corrections when extracting characters.

## Character Name Corrections

| Correct Name | Common Garbled Variants |
|-------------|------------------------|
| **Lunei Milei Maili** | Lunay, Luna, Unai, Leonel, Leo, Lune, Brunein, mi Lady, mi Ley |
| **Tidus** | Tibus, Tidios, Tillus, Tirus, Tiros, Didus, Titi |
| **Nixira** (also Kenitzira / Mai Melody / Melo) | Ni Sira, Mi Sira, My Melo, Melody, My Melody, Listonixina, Zaruma |
| **Farquad** | Facua, Facul, Farf, Lord Far, Pascual |
| **Zacarías** | Zacarías Belmonte, Zacarías Flores |

## Critical Identity Rules

- **Nixira and Melo are the SAME character.** Any references to "Melo", "My Melo", or "Melody" as a separate PC are Nixira.
- **Farquad and Facua are the SAME character.** The tavern patron and the military commander are one person.
- **Lunei Milei Maili** is the tavern boss. Any name that sounds similar (Lunay, Luna, Leonel, etc.) refers to him.

## Ability Attribution

- **Speak with Animals** belongs to **Zacarías** (Warlock), NOT Tidus. If a transcript mentions someone talking to animals, attribute it to Zacarías.
- **Zacarías** also speaks serpentine language ("Pársel") and has Animal Handling.
- **Tidus** does NOT have animal communication abilities. His dragon taming was physical (silence, touch, feeding), not magical.

